author: butek
msg: WSDL describes 4 operation styles:  oneway, request-response, solicit-response,
and notification.  We don't support solicit-response or notification.  I added code to
WSDL2Java to indicate this.  WSDL2Java doesn't fail if it encounters these styles,
it simply prints a comment to the command line and prints comments in the code
where it would normally print the methods.
